# Clerk Billing

All subscription and payment handling uses **Clerk Billing** exclusively. Do not use Stripe directly or any other payment/subscription library.

## Plans & Features

Available **plans** (use exact slugs):
- `free_user`
- `pro`

Available **features** (use exact slugs):
- `3_deck_limit`
- `unlimited_decks`
- `ai_flashcard_generation`

## Pricing Page

Use the `<PricingTable />` component from `@clerk/nextjs` on a dedicated pricing page:

```tsx
import { PricingTable } from '@clerk/nextjs'

export default function PricingPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <PricingTable />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Gating Access — Server Components

Use `has()` from the `auth()` object in Server Components and Server Actions:

```tsx
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'

const { has } = await auth()

// Check plan
const isPro = has({ plan: 'pro' })

// Check feature
const canGenerateAI = has({ feature: 'ai_flashcard_generation' })
const hasUnlimitedDecks = has({ feature: 'unlimited_decks' })
```

## Gating Access — Client / JSX

Use the `<Show>` component from `@clerk/nextjs` to conditionally render UI:

```tsx
import { Show } from '@clerk/nextjs'

<Show
  when={{ feature: 'ai_flashcard_generation' }}
  fallback={<p>Upgrade to Pro to use AI flashcard generation.</p>}
>
  <AIGenerateButton />
</Show>

<Show when={{ plan: 'pro' }} fallback={<UpgradeBanner />}>
  <ProOnlyFeature />
</Show>
```

## Rules

- **Always use `has()` server-side** to enforce access — never trust client-side checks alone.
- **Never hardcode plan/feature logic** outside of `has()` or `<Show>` — always use the Clerk helpers.
- Deck creation must enforce `3_deck_limit` for `free_user` plan users on the server (in Server Actions).
